acceptOwnership().details: used by a new owner to accept an ownership transfer

acceptStoreOwnership().details: accepts the ownership of the store can only be called by the contract owner

acceptWalletOwnership().details: accepts the ownership of the wallet can only be called by the contract owner

addLiquidity(address,address,uint256).details: adds protected liquidity to a pool also mints new governance tokens for the caller if the caller adds network tokens

params.amount: amount of tokens to add to the pool
params.reserveToken: reserve token to add to the pool

addLiquidityFor(address,address,address,.details: adds protected liquidity to a pool for a specific recipient also mints new governance tokens for the caller if the caller adds network tokens

params.amount: amount of tokens to add to the pool
params.reserveToken: reserve token to add to the pool

claimBalance(uint256,uint256).details: allows the caller to claim network token balance that is no longer locked note that the function can revert if the range is too large

params.endIndex: end index in the caller's list of locked balances (exclusive)
params.startIndex: start index in the caller's list of locked balances

poolAvailableSpace(address).details: returns the single-side staking limits of a given pool

returns._0: maximum amount of base tokens that can be single-side staked in the pool
returns._1: maximum amount of network tokens that can be single-side staked in the pool

poolROI(address,address,uint256,uint256,.details: returns the ROI for removing liquidity in the current state after providing liquidity with the given args the function assumes full protection is in effect return value is in PPM and can be larger than PPM_RESOLUTION for positive ROI, 1M = 0% ROI

params.poolRateD: rate of 1 pool token in reserve token units when the liquidity was added (denominator)
params.poolRateN: rate of 1 pool token in reserve token units when the liquidity was added (numerator)
params.reserveAmount: reserve token amount that was added
params.reserveRateD: rate of 1 reserve token in the other reserve token units when the liquidity was added (denominator)
params.reserveRateN: rate of 1 reserve token in the other reserve token units when the liquidity was added (numerator)

removeLiquidity(uint256,uint32).details: removes protected liquidity from a pool also burns governance tokens from the caller if the caller removes network tokens

params.portion: portion of liquidity to remove, in PPM

removeLiquidityReturn(uint256,uint32,uin.details: returns the expected/actual amounts the provider will receive for removing liquidity it's also possible to provide the remove liquidity time to get an estimation for the return at that given point

params.portion: portion of liquidity to remove, in PPM
params.removeTimestamp: time at which the liquidity is removed

returns._0: expected return amount in the reserve token
returns._1: actual return amount in the reserve token

transferOwnership(address).details: allows transferring the contract ownership the new owner still needs to accept the transfer can only be called by the contract owner

transferPosition(uint256,address).details: transfers a position to a new provider

transferPositionAndNotify(uint256,addres.details: transfers a position to a new provider and optionally notifies another contract

params.data: custom data provided to the callback

transferStoreOwnership(address).details: transfers the ownership of the store can only be called by the contract owner

params.newOwner: the new owner of the store

transferWalletOwnership(address).details: transfers the ownership of the wallet can only be called by the contract owner

params.newOwner: the new owner of the wallet
